TopicTitle: [1.2] Kerbal Kommander: a new way to play KSP

Articles.Content:
3 hours ago, gagarinekerman said:

Thank you, if somebody else is interested by creating ship which I can add to the kk savefile, just sent it to me

I could create a stock version of Muna Akademy for you. I also have ideas for several other ground bases.

Also, I just wanted to say, this is an amazing mod. Not just in terms of gameplay fun, but in terms of what it does. You successfully recreated the functionality of EL, added the ability to have a remotely-operated astronaut complex, and created a trading system in your first mod.

New update, 0.1.4:

Changelog:

  • Add ship directly in the save, this ships are made by Veeltch: http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/39636-veeltch/
  • Fix the hire system, it now remove some money;
  • correct "Dimond" to "Diamond";
  • Adding a "refresh" button to the crew hire window to regenerate crew;
  • fix bug that could append when you use a kerbal to open menu;

EDIT:Do you think that the possibility of refresh crew is a good idea ?

Edited June 24, 2016 by gagarinekerman

16 minutes ago, gagarinekerman said:

EDIT:Do you think that the possibility of refresh crew is a good idea ?

I feel like refreshing the crew might lead to exploits. People will refresh it until they get the best member.

Maybe systems further away could have better crews instead?

1 minute ago, Veeltch said:

I feel like refreshing the crew might lead to exploits. People will refresh it until they get the best member.

Maybe systems further away could have better crews instead?

I Do you think it would be better if we had to pay to refresh ?

1 minute ago, gagarinekerman said:

I Do you think it would be better if we had to pay to refresh ?

Dunno. Depends on how much it will cost, I guess.

1 minute ago, Veeltch said:

Dunno. Depends on how much it will cost, I guess.

more and more ?

I've just noticed that the last update is 0.1.4 and that there has never been a 0.1.3 release

rest in peace 0.1.3...

Hey @gagarinekerman! I was trying to minmax my playthrough by recording the prices of every station but, to be honest, it turned into something tantamount to schoolwork quickly. By any chance, could you provide us with one?

Anyways, the mod looks amazing and I can see so much potential! I hope we see bases on every planet (except maybe Eve and Tylo) to mix things up and give you new places to search. Have fun working on the mod! (I guess.)

My work contained within the spoiler. Warning: It's lonnnnnnnng.
